nger-alignment-tool-2021-3-768x666.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08152812/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-alignment-tool-2021-3-696x603.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08152812/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-alignment-tool-2021-3-485x420.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 485w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08152812/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-alignment-tool-2021-3-534x462.jpg?ezimgfmt=ng:webp/ngcb8 534w\"></a></p><p>Compared to the DAG-2.2, the DAG-3 brings Parks derailleur hanger alignment tool into the 21st century with better precision and a more user-friendly design. Now made form an extruded aluminum body, the square steel design is gone in favor of a lighter, round profile.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08152819/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-alignment-tool-2021-4.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08152819/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-alignment-tool-2021-4.jpg\" alt=\"Park Tool derailleur hanger tool DAG 3 gauge\" width=\"900\" height=\"780\" sizes=\"(max-width: 900px) 100vw, 900px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08152819/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-alignment-tool-2021-4.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08152819/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-alignment-tool-2021-4.jpg 900w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/08152819/Park-Tool-DAG-3-derailleur-hanger-alignment-tool-2021-4-297x257.jpg 297w,